WEBVTT

00:01.035 --> 00:03.101
<i> Previously on "nashville"...</i>
We're done.

00:03.103 --> 00:04.669
Why on earth
would you bring your girlfriend

00:04.671 --> 00:07.138
On the road
in a professional capacity?

00:07.140 --> 00:08.339
There are lines
I don't cross.

00:08.341 --> 00:10.207
You're fired.

00:10.209 --> 00:11.675
I am the part owner
in this place.

00:11.677 --> 00:14.277
We're gonna have a bigger stage,
bigger sound system.

00:14.279 --> 00:15.511
Why aren't you
producing my record?

00:15.513 --> 00:17.279
I'm not taking no
for an answer.

00:17.281 --> 00:19.114
You have taken advantage
of our trust,

00:19.116 --> 00:20.615
And we want
to take your phone away.

00:20.617 --> 00:22.683
I saw jeff fordham
fall off the roof last night.

00:22.685 --> 00:24.685
Juliette was out there
like she was going to jump.

00:24.687 --> 00:26.053
We need to keep colt
quiet.

00:26.055 --> 00:27.387
Until we know
what happened --

00:27.389 --> 00:29.122
We know<i> exactly</i> what happened!
I saw it!

00:30.058 --> 00:33.492
¶¶

00:33.494 --> 00:37.195
¶ believe it or not,
I was once like you ¶

00:40.700 --> 00:44.601
¶ now I'm a brick wall
that you can't break through ¶

00:47.138 --> 00:49.638
¶ no, there ain't no cure
for the way I am ¶

00:49.640 --> 00:50.972
[ knock on door ]

00:50.974 --> 00:53.074
Deacon: Maddie?
Can I talk to you a sec?

00:53.876 --> 00:55.675
Hi.
What do you want?

00:55.677 --> 00:58.711
Uh [chuckles] just,
you know, checking in.

00:58.713 --> 00:59.745
Wanted to say
good night.

00:59.747 --> 01:00.912
Okay. Good night.

01:00.914 --> 01:03.180
Um, little late
for a shower, isn't it?

01:03.182 --> 01:05.048
So now I have to ask permission
to wash my hair, too?

01:05.050 --> 01:07.316
No, you don't.
I just --

01:07.318 --> 01:09.151
Look, sweetie, I know you're mad
'cause you're grounded,

01:09.153 --> 01:12.020
But, you know, here we are
in the same house together.

01:12.022 --> 01:14.055
I feel like
I hardly ever even see you.

01:14.057 --> 01:15.156
Yeah.

01:15.158 --> 01:16.390
So, what are you --

01:16.392 --> 01:18.925
I was just thinking
maybe we could, um,

01:18.927 --> 01:21.928
Start up with guitar lessons
again, you know?

01:21.930 --> 01:23.496
Hang out a little more,
like we used to.

01:24.732 --> 01:25.764
Can we talk about this
later?

01:25.766 --> 01:27.065
Okay. Yeah, sure.

01:27.067 --> 01:29.067
Okay. Good night.

01:29.069 --> 01:30.535
Maddie!

01:30.537 --> 01:32.703
What are you doing?
Why are you out of bed, sweetie?

01:32.705 --> 01:33.704
I can't find my phone.

01:33.706 --> 01:35.739
Stupid maddie
must have taken it again.

01:35.741 --> 01:37.340
Take it easy, all right?
You're not going in there
right now.

01:37.342 --> 01:39.041
You don't even need your phone
tonight. It's bedtime.

01:39.043 --> 01:40.942
I'll help you find it
in the morning. It's okay.

01:40.944 --> 01:43.210
When's my mom
coming home?

01:43.212 --> 01:44.778
[ scoffs ]

01:44.780 --> 01:46.813
[ "all I want is us tonight"
plays ]

01:51.352 --> 01:53.852
¶ wear your pretty black dress
or your faded blue jeans ¶

01:53.854 --> 01:56.521
¶ high heels
or your pretty bare feet ¶

01:56.523 --> 01:58.422
¶ wear what you want, baby ¶

01:58.424 --> 02:01.591
¶ it's you I wanna see ¶

02:01.593 --> 02:03.426
¶ nobody around us ¶

02:03.428 --> 02:07.096
¶ only the sound of hearts
and a raging fire ¶

02:07.098 --> 02:11.567
¶ slowly melts in the sky ¶

02:11.569 --> 02:16.404
¶ all I want is us tonight ¶
[ cellphone dings ]

02:16.406 --> 02:19.306
¶ all of our dreams,
all of our secrets ¶

02:19.308 --> 02:21.941
¶ nothing tonight's
gonna come between us ¶

02:21.943 --> 02:26.878
¶ pull you close,
you close your eyes ¶

02:26.880 --> 02:29.747
¶ kiss your lips,
hold you tight ¶

02:29.749 --> 02:31.982
¶ all I want is ¶

02:31.984 --> 02:34.150
¶ all I want is ¶

02:34.152 --> 02:40.189
¶ all I want is us tonight ¶

02:43.427 --> 02:44.926
That's the one.
That's the one.

02:44.928 --> 02:46.928
That's it. Yes!

02:46.930 --> 02:47.962
That right there was magic.

02:47.964 --> 02:49.563
That was great.
Right?

02:49.565 --> 02:51.498
Oh, my god, I owe it all to you,
rayna jaymes.

02:51.500 --> 02:54.267
You're the best damn producer
in the business.
[ laughs ]

02:54.269 --> 02:56.402
So, what's next?
Sleep.

02:56.404 --> 02:57.903
We can't go to sleep.
We're on a roll, baby.

02:57.905 --> 02:59.104
Do you know
it's 6:00 in the morning?

02:59.106 --> 03:00.438
Yeah,
I know what time it is.

03:00.440 --> 03:01.972
We've been doing this
for practically 24 hours.

03:01.974 --> 03:03.239
So what's
another couple hours?

03:03.241 --> 03:04.740
No.
Everybody's exhausted.

03:04.742 --> 03:06.274
I will send somebody
on a coffee run. I'll even buy.

03:06.276 --> 03:07.675
I don't need
another latte.

03:07.677 --> 03:09.510
I'm gonna have to
take my kids to school.

03:09.512 --> 03:10.844
You killed it.
Thank you.

03:10.846 --> 03:12.812
It is beautiful.
I'm so excited.

03:12.814 --> 03:13.913
Let these people go home.

03:13.915 --> 03:15.447
Y'all, thank you.

03:15.449 --> 03:18.616
We're calling it.
Get some rest.

03:18.618 --> 03:19.917
[ sighs ]

03:19.919 --> 03:21.852
[ both laugh ]

03:21.854 --> 03:23.686
You exhaust me.

03:26.323 --> 03:28.523
Dude, some great reviews
out of buffalo and albany.

03:28.525 --> 03:30.458
Yeah!
And I just spoke
to the boston promoter.

03:30.460 --> 03:31.792
Looks like both nights
are sold out.

03:31.794 --> 03:32.659
That's so great.

03:32.661 --> 03:34.093
Back-to-back shows means

03:34.095 --> 03:35.427
We actually get
hotel rooms tonight, right?

03:36.830 --> 03:39.297
What? Four nights on a bus,
I'm ready for a real bed.

03:39.299 --> 03:40.798
[ cellphone ringing ]

03:40.800 --> 03:42.366
Need to take that?

03:42.368 --> 03:43.867
Uh, no. I can call him back
when we're done. It's okay.

03:43.869 --> 03:45.301
What else we got?

03:45.303 --> 03:46.769
Well, let's see.

03:46.771 --> 03:48.604
Bucky's arranged a few more
drive times down the road,

03:48.606 --> 03:49.938
And noel's
gonna get back to me

03:49.940 --> 03:52.540
About setting up a couple more
interviews and signings.

03:52.542 --> 03:53.541
That sounds so good.

03:54.644 --> 03:56.276
Ow!
What? I'm listening.

03:56.278 --> 03:58.778
Signings -- awesome.
Anything else?

03:58.780 --> 03:59.945
Nope.
That's all I got.

03:59.947 --> 04:01.546
Should be in boston
in a couple hours.

04:04.784 --> 04:07.017
By the way, I've been meaning
to say something all week.

04:07.019 --> 04:09.119
I'm impressed --
the confidence, the drive.

04:09.121 --> 04:11.154
Definitely not the same scarlett
I tour-managed

04:11.156 --> 04:12.288
Your first time out.

04:12.290 --> 04:14.323
Thank you.
It's real good to be back.

04:14.325 --> 04:16.191
The success of this band
means a lot to me.

04:16.193 --> 04:18.392
Erin:
[ laughing ] stop!

04:20.362 --> 04:22.695
Just hoping
everybody feels the same way.

04:24.665 --> 04:26.398
Will: Uh...

04:26.400 --> 04:27.799
Uh, hang on!
Just a sec!

04:29.469 --> 04:31.402
[ door unlocks ]

04:31.404 --> 04:32.536
Hey.

04:32.538 --> 04:34.671
What's, uh...
What's up, man?

04:34.673 --> 04:35.705
[ chuckles nervously ]

04:35.707 --> 04:37.373
You okay?

04:37.375 --> 04:39.475
I haven't, uh, seen
or talked to you in a few days.

04:39.477 --> 04:41.910
Yeah, totally.
All good.

04:41.912 --> 04:44.212
Yeah. Uh...
You need something?

04:44.214 --> 04:46.814
I got this, uh,
studio gig today,

04:46.816 --> 04:48.549
And emily's running
a few minutes late.

04:48.551 --> 04:50.717
Can you listen to cadence for me
till she gets back?

04:50.719 --> 04:52.418
Oh, yeah, sure.
Yeah. No problem.

04:52.420 --> 04:53.719
You sure?

04:53.721 --> 04:55.153
I mean,
I don't want to interrupt

04:55.155 --> 04:56.187
Whatever it is
you got going on.

04:56.189 --> 04:57.855
No, no. That's --
that's not a problem.

04:57.857 --> 04:59.223
Have fun at your gig.

05:10.736 --> 05:12.102
[ exhales deeply ]

05:12.104 --> 05:15.205
So, uh, how'd it go?
He say anything?

05:15.207 --> 05:18.274
Mr. Wheeler, your son
is incredibly withdrawn.

05:18.276 --> 05:20.709
He barely spoke
the entire session.

05:20.711 --> 05:21.576
Right.

05:21.578 --> 05:23.110
But it's quite possible

05:23.112 --> 05:25.212
He just wasn't
feeling comfortable with me.

05:25.214 --> 05:27.380
No.
No, I don't think so.

05:27.382 --> 05:30.583
You're the fourth therapist
to say that this week.

05:30.585 --> 05:33.919
Well, I think it's important
that colt talk to someone.

05:33.921 --> 05:36.721
This level of detachment
speaks to trust issues

05:36.723 --> 05:38.389
That really need
to be dealt with.

05:38.391 --> 05:40.457
I'd be happy to refer you
to another specialist

05:40.459 --> 05:42.192
Wherever your tour
takes you next.

05:42.194 --> 05:43.693
Yeah, that'd be great.
I really appreciate it, doc.

05:43.695 --> 05:44.994
Thanks.

05:49.633 --> 05:51.366
[ sighs ]

05:51.368 --> 05:53.101
[ knock on door ]

05:53.103 --> 05:54.769
[ door opens ]

05:54.771 --> 05:57.304
I take it you didn't like
that one, either?

05:57.306 --> 05:59.205
Didn't want a therapist
in milwaukee.

05:59.207 --> 06:01.006
Don't know why I'd want one
in philadelphia.

06:02.476 --> 06:04.609
Listen, I was, um...

06:04.611 --> 06:06.911
Thinking you might be interested
in coming to my show tonight.

06:06.913 --> 06:09.380
Kid rock is filling in
as my opener,

06:09.382 --> 06:12.549
And I was talking to him about
how much you're into hip-hop.

06:12.551 --> 06:14.284
He said
he'd really like to meet you.

06:14.286 --> 06:15.618
What do you think
about that?

06:15.620 --> 06:17.453
No, thanks.

06:17.455 --> 06:20.756
Colt, come on. A little fun
might be good for you.

06:20.758 --> 06:23.892
I don't need fun or kid rock
or any other stupid therapists.

06:23.894 --> 06:25.627
Then help me out, son.
Tell me what you do need.

06:25.629 --> 06:29.063
'cause, um...I'm nearing
the end of my rope here.

06:29.065 --> 06:31.031
I need a dad who gives a crap
about telling the truth.

06:34.936 --> 06:37.635
[ door opens ]

06:38.404 --> 06:39.836
There she is.

06:39.838 --> 06:41.337
I'll tell you what --

06:41.339 --> 06:43.238
I think this producing
is about to kill me.

06:43.240 --> 06:44.472
Not for the faint of heart,
is it?

06:44.474 --> 06:45.739
No, it is not.

06:45.741 --> 06:47.440
Markus giving you
a hard time?

06:47.442 --> 06:50.242
You know, it's just sort of like
having a third kid.

06:50.244 --> 06:51.276
[ both chuckle ]

06:51.278 --> 06:51.909
Man.

06:53.479 --> 06:55.078
Two's hard enough.
[ chuckles ]

06:55.080 --> 06:56.345
Yeah.

06:56.347 --> 06:57.846
Are they up and going?

06:57.848 --> 06:59.614
Well, daphne is,
but maddie...

06:59.616 --> 07:02.283
I don't know. I can't get
two words out of her.

07:02.285 --> 07:03.417
Yeah, I know that story.

07:03.419 --> 07:04.851
Thank you for taking
such good care of them

07:04.853 --> 07:06.085
These last couple days.

07:06.087 --> 07:07.619
You got it.

07:07.621 --> 07:09.020
Can I ask you
a big favor?

07:09.022 --> 07:10.488
You mind driving them to school
for me this morning?

07:10.490 --> 07:12.423
Oh, baby, I can't.
I got to get down to the bar.

07:12.425 --> 07:14.091
We're getting the sign
delivered today

07:14.093 --> 07:15.625
And knocking out
a whole wall.

07:15.627 --> 07:16.626
I'm supervising
everything.

07:16.628 --> 07:17.693
They're waiting for me
right now.

07:17.695 --> 07:18.760
Okay.

07:18.762 --> 07:19.994
Sorry.

07:19.996 --> 07:21.261
It's all right.

07:21.263 --> 07:23.162
See you tonight.

07:23.164 --> 07:25.063
Yep. Hope so.
All right.

07:26.466 --> 07:28.299
Girls!

07:28.301 --> 07:29.933
[ door closes ]

07:29.935 --> 07:32.168
You don't have to yell.
I'm right here.

07:32.170 --> 07:34.270
Did you dye your hair?

07:34.272 --> 07:36.005
What? So now
my hair's grounded, too?

07:36.007 --> 07:38.040
Okay, if you're trying to get
a rise out of me this morning,

07:38.042 --> 07:39.474
Just forget it.
[ telephone rings ]

07:39.476 --> 07:40.975
I'm not even gonna discuss this
with you right now.

07:40.977 --> 07:42.309
We'll talk about it tonight
with your father.

07:42.311 --> 07:44.878
Go get your stuff
together -- now.

07:44.880 --> 07:46.512
Hey, buck.

07:46.514 --> 07:51.116
Rayna, I'm looking at 160 hours
of overtime at the studio.

07:51.118 --> 07:52.784
Dare I ask how things
are going over there?

07:52.786 --> 07:55.153
You know, I think we've got
some amazing tracks.

07:55.155 --> 07:56.621
I'm not sure
when I'm ever gonna sleep again.

07:56.623 --> 07:57.855
Well, I hope
you get it done quick,

07:57.857 --> 07:59.122
Since we're gonna
have to push

07:59.124 --> 08:00.556
Layla's album launch back
indefinitely.

08:00.558 --> 08:01.957
Have you heard from her?

08:01.959 --> 08:03.658
She's up in connecticut still
with her family.

08:03.660 --> 08:05.059
She's not coming back
anytime soon.

08:05.061 --> 08:06.493
Listen,
can I call you back?

08:06.495 --> 08:10.029
I've [groans] got a little
teen crisis going on here.

08:10.031 --> 08:11.964
Yeah, actually,
the other reason I'm calling is

08:11.966 --> 08:14.499
Because there's been an inquiry
from an a&r exec at sony

08:14.501 --> 08:15.867
Asking about maddie.

08:15.869 --> 08:17.401
They want to sign her.
What?

08:17.403 --> 08:18.568
Yeah, apparently,
they saw a clip

08:18.570 --> 08:20.903
Of her singing with juliette
in atlanta,

08:20.905 --> 08:22.804
And they are interested in her
as a solo artist.

08:22.806 --> 08:24.205
She's 16 years old.

08:24.207 --> 08:26.240
She's not signing
a solo deal with sony.

08:26.242 --> 08:27.174
What?

08:27.176 --> 08:28.375
Buck, I'll call you back.
Bye.

08:28.377 --> 08:29.909
Wait. I got an offer?

08:29.911 --> 08:31.477
Were you even
gonna tell me?

08:31.479 --> 08:33.545
I'm sure I was, but, maddie,
we've discussed this.

08:33.547 --> 08:35.313
No, mom, we haven't!

08:35.315 --> 08:37.081
Sony wants me?!

08:37.083 --> 08:38.582
Why won't you let me sign?

08:38.584 --> 08:41.217
For so many reasons,
including you're too young!

08:41.219 --> 08:43.352
You are ruining my life,
mom!

08:43.354 --> 08:45.320
You're trying to keep me
from doing the things I love,

08:45.322 --> 08:46.721
But you can't, okay?

08:46.723 --> 08:48.822
You just can't!

08:51.493 --> 08:55.294
¶¶

09:01.701 --> 09:02.900
<i> You've reached dr. Caleb rand.</i>

09:02.902 --> 09:03.700
<i> Please leave a message</i>
<i> after the tone.</i>

09:03.702 --> 09:05.368
Sorry I missed you before.

09:05.370 --> 09:07.103
Uh, I got some time
before sound check, though,

09:07.105 --> 09:08.904
So give me a call back.

09:08.906 --> 09:11.373
Hey. So, uh,
w-what are you up to?

09:11.375 --> 09:13.541
Well, they have me bunking
with carly,

09:13.543 --> 09:15.876
So we're gonna go check in,
rest in our room for a little

09:15.878 --> 09:17.577
Before we head to the venue
for setup.

09:17.579 --> 09:20.346
Yeah. That -- that makes sense.
[ chuckles ]

09:20.348 --> 09:23.549
You're welcome to make me
a better offer, though.

09:23.551 --> 09:25.017
Okay, um...

09:25.019 --> 09:28.587
Well, I know we said
work is work and play is play,

09:28.589 --> 09:33.191
But I got a hotel room
to myself, and...

09:33.193 --> 09:35.726
We're not working
for a while, so...

09:35.728 --> 09:37.360
Yeah.

