Okay, got it.

10:23.262 --> 10:24.828
Give me a second, and I'll
set up for the next one.

10:24.830 --> 10:26.229
Oh, thank god.

10:26.231 --> 10:28.064
Okay, yeah.
I-I'm gonna make a quick call.

10:28.066 --> 10:28.898
Sounds good.

10:32.069 --> 10:35.103
[ sighs deeply ]

10:35.105 --> 10:36.104
[ ringing ]

10:36.106 --> 10:37.238
Emily: Hey, avery.

10:37.240 --> 10:38.639
Hello. [ sighs ]

10:38.641 --> 10:40.407
Hey, I'm just, uh,
calling to make sure,

10:40.409 --> 10:43.343
Uh, the handoff with will
went okay this morning.

10:43.345 --> 10:45.345
Yep. It went fine.
Cadence and I are at the park.

10:45.347 --> 10:46.813
Oh, good.

10:46.815 --> 10:49.849
So, when you saw will,
was he acting weird at all?

10:49.851 --> 10:51.984
Well, he seemed
a little quiet. Why?

10:51.986 --> 10:54.953
He's been kind of...Cagey
all week --

10:54.955 --> 10:56.955
Actually,
since he and kevin split up.

10:56.957 --> 10:58.690
Aw. They're not together
anymore?

10:58.692 --> 10:59.991
I liked kevin.

10:59.993 --> 11:02.326
Yeah, me too,
but I'm beginning to think

11:02.328 --> 11:04.161
Will's already got
someone else.

11:04.163 --> 11:05.462
Whoa. That was fast.

11:05.464 --> 11:08.431
I mean, I haven't exactly seen
anyone coming or going,

11:08.433 --> 11:10.433
But how would I?

11:10.435 --> 11:13.102
Half the time, I fall asleep
putting cadence to bed at night.

11:13.104 --> 11:15.604
Maybe that's
when he's bringing company in.

11:15.606 --> 11:17.005
Well, everybody has
their own way

11:17.007 --> 11:18.539
Of getting over a breakup,
I guess.

11:18.541 --> 11:20.507
Yeah, I guess.

11:24.312 --> 11:26.378
I tell you
what we can do.

11:26.380 --> 11:28.780
If we just turn the pool table
sideways like that,

11:28.782 --> 11:30.214
Then we get a whole nother row
of the pews in right there.

11:30.216 --> 11:31.381
What do you think?
Good idea.

11:31.383 --> 11:32.615
Let me get
some measurements.

11:32.617 --> 11:33.983
When I get back,
we'll talk paint.

11:33.985 --> 11:36.485
All right.
Talking paint, man.

11:36.487 --> 11:39.554
Nice to make
some progress here, huh?
Yep.

11:39.556 --> 11:42.490
At this rate, we'll be
re-opening a hell of a lot
sooner than we thought.

11:42.492 --> 11:43.290
[ cellphone rings ]
yeah,
you're not kidding.

11:43.292 --> 11:44.557
Oh. Hold on.

11:44.559 --> 11:46.559
Hey, baby.
What's going on?

11:46.561 --> 11:48.661
Hey. Been trying to reach you
all morning. Where you been?

11:48.663 --> 11:51.330
Oh, I'm sorry, baby.
I got a real noisy crew in here.

11:51.332 --> 11:53.365
I didn't hear your call.
What do you need?

11:53.367 --> 11:55.700
Well, first of all,
maddie dyed her hair.
Did you know that?

11:55.702 --> 11:58.069
[ sighs ] lord. No.

11:58.071 --> 12:00.738
I did not know about that,
rayna. I'm sorry.

12:00.740 --> 12:05.241
She just had her hair in a towel
all night, and I...

12:05.243 --> 12:06.308
[ sighs ]

12:06.310 --> 12:07.642
How's it look?

12:07.644 --> 12:09.910
She looks like she's trying
to be juliette barnes.

12:09.912 --> 12:11.211
And now we got
a bigger issue

12:11.213 --> 12:13.479
Because sony wants
to offer her a record deal.

12:13.481 --> 12:16.081
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.
How does sony even know
that they want to sign her?

12:16.083 --> 12:17.849
Because of
the stupid video.

12:17.851 --> 12:19.584
So, how do you want
to handle it?

12:19.586 --> 12:22.420
I don't know. I'm just --
I'm so confused at this point.

12:22.422 --> 12:23.587
She's so defiant.

12:23.589 --> 12:24.888
Frankie. The sign.
You know, we've got to --

12:24.890 --> 12:26.422
We got to talk to her.

12:26.424 --> 12:28.023
All right, listen, baby,

12:28.025 --> 12:30.759
Whatever you decide,
I will back you 100%, all right?

12:30.761 --> 12:34.429
Oh, okay, but I-I actually could
really use -- if we just --

12:34.431 --> 12:36.330
Sweetie, they're delivering
the sign right now.

12:36.332 --> 12:37.564
We'll talk later
about it all, okay?

12:37.566 --> 12:38.831
I love you.
Got to go.

12:38.833 --> 12:39.832
Bye.

12:45.539 --> 12:47.705
You, uh,
you like lattes, right?

12:47.707 --> 12:50.274
[ chuckles ]

12:50.276 --> 12:52.342
Oh, man,
that is pretty.

12:52.344 --> 12:53.676
Yeah, it is.
No. I'm serious.

12:53.678 --> 12:55.077
That is a beautiful sign
right here.

12:55.079 --> 12:56.278
When's it going up?

12:56.280 --> 12:57.579
I got a crew coming in
tomorrow afternoon.

12:57.581 --> 12:59.213
They're gonna put it up.

12:59.215 --> 13:02.549
Not much we can do till
they get that wall knocked down,

13:02.551 --> 13:04.284
So shall we call it a day?

13:04.286 --> 13:06.052
Call it a d--

13:06.054 --> 13:08.354
Man, we got a grand opening
coming up, all right?

13:08.356 --> 13:09.788
I know there's plenty
that we got to do here.

13:09.790 --> 13:11.122
We got to be ready.

13:11.124 --> 13:12.857
I want everything
to be perfect.

13:12.859 --> 13:14.825
Just perfect.

13:16.361 --> 13:17.360
[ knock on door ]

13:17.362 --> 13:19.862
[ water running ]

13:19.864 --> 13:21.363
Oh. Sorry.

13:21.365 --> 13:23.898
Oh. I was about to
hop in the shower. What's up?

13:23.900 --> 13:26.233
I'm headed down to the venue
to say hi to some fans.

13:26.235 --> 13:28.068
Like a --
a meet-and-greet?

13:28.070 --> 13:30.403
I don't remember that
being on the schedule.
I-it wasn't.

13:30.405 --> 13:32.071
Shep just told me they're
already lining up for the show,

13:32.073 --> 13:33.605
And I thought
we could go down, tell them

13:33.607 --> 13:35.239
How much we appreciate them,
if you want to come.

13:35.241 --> 13:36.940
Yeah. Sounds good.
Uh, let me just --

13:36.942 --> 13:39.007
Erin: Gunnar!
You coming in?

13:40.276 --> 13:42.242
Uh...

13:42.244 --> 13:44.978
You know what? I will, uh,
catch up to you, okay?

13:49.951 --> 13:51.417
No, let's leave
"it's on tonight"
where it is --

13:51.419 --> 13:52.718
In the encore.

13:52.720 --> 13:53.585
Hey.

13:53.587 --> 13:54.752
Hey.

13:54.754 --> 13:56.086
I-I'm not interrupting?

13:56.088 --> 13:57.954
No. Just, uh,
going over the set list.

13:57.956 --> 13:59.422
How was new york?
Flight okay?

13:59.424 --> 14:00.556
Good. Yeah.

14:00.558 --> 14:02.124
Um,
could we have the room

14:02.126 --> 14:04.426
Just to go over
some business matters?

14:04.428 --> 14:05.760
Yeah, sure. Hey, give us
a few minutes, guys, will you?

14:05.762 --> 14:06.961
Thanks.

14:06.963 --> 14:08.028
Let's go, boys.

14:12.567 --> 14:13.666
[ door closes ]

14:14.669 --> 14:16.502
Any word on juliette?

14:16.504 --> 14:18.637
Yeah. I checked in
with the clinic this morning.

14:18.639 --> 14:20.972
She's still in detox, but as
soon as she's done with that,

14:20.974 --> 14:22.907
She can start working
on her recovery.

14:22.909 --> 14:26.410
But I think it's best we find
a replacement for the tour.

14:26.412 --> 14:28.945
I also think we should start
looking for a new c.E.O.

14:28.947 --> 14:30.746
For the brand
as soon as possible.

14:30.748 --> 14:33.682
[ exhales sharply ]

14:33.684 --> 14:34.582
[ sighs ]

14:34.584 --> 14:36.350
I can't believe all this.

14:38.954 --> 14:41.521
Juliette spiraling,
jeff dying,

14:41.523 --> 14:44.423
My son pushing me out.

14:44.425 --> 14:47.859
I feel like a hell of a lot of
pain has happened on my watch.

14:50.196 --> 14:52.196
It's hard
not to feel responsible.

14:52.198 --> 14:53.263
Hey.

14:53.265 --> 14:54.697
What?

14:54.699 --> 14:56.465
None of that
is your fault.

14:56.467 --> 14:58.867
You are a good father,
a good man.

14:58.869 --> 15:01.135
You are doing
the best you can.

15:01.137 --> 15:02.136
Am I?

15:02.138 --> 15:03.570
Yes.

15:18.119 --> 15:19.818
Wait.
We shouldn't.

15:19.820 --> 15:20.885
What?
I don't get it.

15:20.887 --> 15:22.653
That time
a-at the party --

15:22.655 --> 15:24.655
We were coming off
of a celebration.

15:24.657 --> 15:25.956
But after everything
that happened,

15:25.958 --> 15:28.358
I told myself that
that would be the last time.

15:28.360 --> 15:29.325
And why is that?

15:29.327 --> 15:30.826
Because
this is inappropriate,

15:30.828 --> 15:32.627
Allowing our work relationship
to become --

15:32.629 --> 15:33.527
Become a real one?

15:33.529 --> 15:35.028
I got to say,

15:35.030 --> 15:36.529
I-I'm getting a little tired
of the business talk.

15:36.531 --> 15:38.030
I want to know
how you actually feel.

15:38.032 --> 15:40.799
Because I like you,
gabriella,

15:40.801 --> 15:44.635
A-and I'm pretty sure
that you...

15:44.637 --> 15:46.303
Might just like me,
as well.

15:47.973 --> 15:49.706
Look, you've been
the one good thing

15:49.708 --> 15:52.575
To come out of this tour --
out of any of this.

15:52.577 --> 15:54.143
Let's give this a shot.

15:54.145 --> 15:55.744
Okay.

15:58.248 --> 16:01.649
But I still think it's
in both of our best interests

16:01.651 --> 16:03.384
To keep this quiet.

16:03.386 --> 16:05.552
I'm not exactly good
for your brand.

16:05.554 --> 16:07.487
My brand.

16:07.489 --> 16:11.190
Okay, I will follow your lead
as far as p.R. Is concerned,

16:11.192 --> 16:13.859
But I'm not keeping this
from colt,

16:13.861 --> 16:15.659
If that's all right
with you.

16:17.529 --> 16:19.262
[ exhales deeply ]

16:19.264 --> 16:20.863
[ camera clicks ]
I love your new look.

16:20.865 --> 16:22.698
Thank you.
You're sweet.

16:22.700 --> 16:24.266
I really dig your music.

16:24.268 --> 16:25.700
So glad
the tour came to boston.

16:25.702 --> 16:26.901
Thank you.
We're so happy to be here.

16:26.903 --> 16:28.402
There you go.
Thank you.

16:28.404 --> 16:29.503
Hey, scarlett.
Yeah?

16:29.505 --> 16:30.904
It's about time
for sound check.

16:30.906 --> 16:32.538
Okay.
You guys, I got to go.

16:32.540 --> 16:33.739
I'll see you out there.
Thank you so much for coming.

16:33.741 --> 16:34.840
[ crowd groans ]

16:36.543 --> 16:38.442
Good idea,
coming out earlier.

16:38.444 --> 16:40.243
That's how
you really build a fan base.

16:40.245 --> 16:41.510
That's the point.

16:41.512 --> 16:43.378
I really like
meeting them, too.

16:43.380 --> 16:44.679
[ cellphone ringing ]

16:44.681 --> 16:46.247
Hang on. Sorry.

16:46.249 --> 16:47.715
Hey, you.

16:47.717 --> 16:49.283
Surprised I finally caught you.
How are you?

16:49.285 --> 16:50.584
Can you talk?

16:50.586 --> 16:53.086
Uh, I can't right now.
I got to step into sound check.

16:53.088 --> 16:55.254
Now? It can't wait?

16:55.256 --> 16:57.623
Not really. Can I call you back
in 20 minutes?

16:57.625 --> 16:59.558
Uh, I'm seeing
an 8-year-old patient

16:59.560 --> 17:01.026
With lymphoma by then,
so no.

17:02.896 --> 17:04.462
I-I know you're doing
really important work.

17:04.464 --> 17:06.096
Um, I'm working, too.

17:06.098 --> 17:08.364
Just now is not --
not a real good time. I'm sorry.

17:08.366 --> 17:09.732
Okay.
When would be?

17:09.734 --> 17:11.533
We haven't found one
since you left.

17:11.535 --> 17:13.034
We talked about this.

17:13.036 --> 17:14.368
It's gonna be hard
to make our schedules link up,

17:14.370 --> 17:16.403
But we just
got to keep trying.

17:16.405 --> 17:19.105
Yeah, well [scoffs]
I<i> am</i> trying.

17:19.107 --> 17:21.240
I'm starting to feel
like the only one who is.

17:21.242 --> 17:22.574
That's not true or fair.

17:22.576 --> 17:23.675
[ chuckles ]

17:25.645 --> 17:27.277
I'm sorry.
It's just --

17:27.279 --> 17:28.878
Scarlett!
We're ready for you!

17:30.114 --> 17:32.247
Caleb, I have to go.
I'll talk to you soon.

17:32.249 --> 17:33.915
Bye.

17:33.917 --> 17:35.650
Okay, let's get going.

17:35.652 --> 17:37.218
Uh, erin,
would you mind making sure

17:37.220 --> 17:39.320
That my vocal is turned up
and completely isolated

17:39.322 --> 17:40.921
In my monitors tonight,
please?

17:40.923 --> 17:42.489
Yeah. They<i> have</i> been.
Oh, okay.

17:42.491 --> 17:44.290
It's just a little hard to hear
them the last couple shows.

17:44.292 --> 17:45.324
Would you mind checking?

17:45.326 --> 17:46.657
She knows what she's doing,
scarlett.

17:49.495 --> 17:50.794
Is everything
all right?

17:50.796 --> 17:52.929
You seem, uh,
a little tense today.

17:52.931 --> 17:56.299
Nope. Just trying
to put on a good show.

17:56.301 --> 17:57.333
That's all.

17:57.335 --> 18:00.436
[ mid-tempo music plays ]

18:00.438 --> 18:01.637
Markus:
<i> How was that?</i>

18:03.440 --> 18:05.973
Can you just do that last verse
for me one more time, please?

18:05.975 --> 18:08.742
<i> [ chuckles ] rayna, I-I just</i>
<i> did that like five times.</i>

18:08.744 --> 18:10.977
I'm sorry.
Just -- sorry.

18:10.979 --> 18:12.578
<i> Why don't we take a break?</i>

18:12.580 --> 18:13.745
<i> How about that?</i>

18:14.948 --> 18:16.981
All right.
Um, thanks, guys.

18:20.352 --> 18:21.751
What's up?

18:21.753 --> 18:23.185
You're not vibing it
today?

18:23.187 --> 18:24.619
No, it's -- it's great.

18:24.621 --> 18:26.753
It's -- it's not you.
I'm just a little preoccupied.

18:28.857 --> 18:30.590
Lay it on me, sister.

18:30.592 --> 18:31.991
Well, don't ever have kids.
I'll tell you that much.

18:31.993 --> 18:33.292
Are we talking
about maddie?

18:33.294 --> 18:34.860
Yeah.
Yeah? What's she doing?

18:34.862 --> 18:36.595
She throwing keggers
or stealing cars?

18:36.597 --> 18:39.164
[ chuckles ] no. She was offered
a record deal at sony.

18:39.166 --> 18:40.965
Well, I mean, I can't say
I'm surprised, you know.

18:40.967 --> 18:42.766
She blew me away
with the cover of my song.

18:42.768 --> 18:45.769
My girls are
so incredibly talented.

18:45.771 --> 18:48.037
It's just maddie
wants it all right now.
[ chuckling ] yeah.

18:48.039 --> 18:50.506
You know, and I see her
in that video with juliette,

18:50.508 --> 18:52.941
And I know that she thinks
she can just go down that road

18:52.943 --> 18:54.776
And all her dreams
are gonna come true.

18:54.778 --> 18:56.210
Yeah, and at their age,
you know,

18:56.212 --> 18:59.713
All they see is
famous friends and private jets.

18:59.715 --> 19:01.314
But what they don't see

19:01.316 --> 19:04.550
Is that it's a distorted view
of the world, you know,

19:04.552 --> 19:06.618
And pretty soon,
you forget who you are

19:06.620 --> 19:08.987
Or why you even got in
the business to begin with.

19:08.989 --> 19:10.221
That's if you make it,
you know?

19:10.223 --> 19:12.856
It's not all it's cracked up
to be sometimes, huh?

19:14.292 --> 19:16.224
Sometimes it isn't.

19:18.161 --> 19:20.361
Will?

19:20.363 --> 19:21.362
Hey. Uh...

19:21.364 --> 19:22.796
[ door closes ]

19:22.798 --> 19:24.497
Sorry. I didn't realize
you were home.

19:24.499 --> 19:27.032
Wait, is this what you've been
doing this whole time --

19:27.034 --> 19:28.066
Writing songs?

19:28.068 --> 19:29.801
Maybe.
Thank god.

19:29.803 --> 19:32.570
I was starting to think you had
someone locked in your room.

19:32.572 --> 19:34.605
What? No. No. I --

19:35.708 --> 19:37.007
I don't know.

19:37.009 --> 19:40.043
I just thought
this might help me

19:40.045 --> 19:44.179
Sort through some feelings
about kevin,

19:44.181 --> 19:46.147
About...

19:47.483 --> 19:50.250
[ exhales sharply ] forget it.
It's -- it's a dumb idea.

19:50.252 --> 19:51.751
It's not dumb.

19:51.753 --> 19:53.419
You're going through
a breakup.

19:53.421 --> 19:55.754
May as well put it
to some good use.

19:55.756 --> 19:57.522
That's what artists do.

19:57.524 --> 19:59.257
Why keep it a secret?

19:59.259 --> 20:01.592
'cause I'm terrible
at it.

20:01.594 --> 20:04.061
I mean...
[ scoffs ]

20:04.063 --> 20:05.729
The only thing I ever wrote,
I wrote with kevin.

20:05.731 --> 20:07.397
Let me see.
No, no, no!

20:07.399 --> 20:09.565
